  • Cement is slightly left skewed
  • Slag is left skewed with minimal outliers on the right
  • Course Agg and Fine Agg are pretty well distributed
  • Water is slightly right skewed with a few outliers on each end
  • Ash is left skewed with a pretty high number of zeroes
  • Age is left skewed with some outliers on the right
  • strenght is pretty decently distributed with some outliers on the right

Feature Engineering¶

We can replace coarseagg and fineagg with the ratio between the two

In [64]:
df['aggregatesratio'] = df['coarseagg']/df['fineagg']
df.drop(columns=['coarseagg','fineagg'], inplace=True)

Model Train Test Split

In [65]:
X = df.drop('strength', axis=1)
y = df[['strength']]
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split
X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X, y, test_size = .30, random_state=0)

Model Complexity:

In [66]:
from sklearn.preprocessing import PolynomialFeatures
from sklearn.linear_model import LinearRegression
from sklearn import linear_model

regression_model = LinearRegression()
regression_model.fit(X_train, y_train)
linearScore = regression_model.score(X_test, y_test)
print('linear:', linearScore)

linear: 0.5820356828403357
In [67]:
poly2 = PolynomialFeatures(degree=2)
X_train2 = poly2.fit_transform(X_train)
X_test2 = poly2.fit_transform(X_test)

poly_clf = linear_model.LinearRegression()

poly_clf.fit(X_train2, y_train)

y_pred = poly_clf.predict(X_test2)
print('Quadratic:',poly_clf.score(X_train2, y_train))

Quadratic: 0.8094075948155774
In [68]:

poly_clf3.fit(X_train3, y_train)

Model Creation and Tuning¶

In [69]:
from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler
from sklearn.decomposition import PCA
from sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression
from sklearn.ensemble import GradientBoostingRegressor
from sklearn.model_selection import KFold
from sklearn.model_selection import cross_val_score
num_folds = 50
seed = 7
kfold = KFold(n_splits=num_folds, random_state=seed)

# dataframe to hold results of all the different classifiers
Results = pd.DataFrame(columns=['Type','Score'], data=[])
Results.head()


from sklearn.pipeline import Pipeline

pipe_lr = Pipeline([('scl', StandardScaler()), ('pca', PCA()), ('gbr', GradientBoostingRegressor(random_state=seed))])

results = cross_val_score(pipe_lr, X, y, cv=kfold)
print("Gradient Boosting Accuracy: %.3f%% (%.3f%%)" % (results.mean()*100.0, results.std()*100.0))
Results = Results.append([{'Type':'Gradient Boosting Regressor','Score':results.mean()*100.0}])

Gradient Boosting Accuracy: 76.899% (9.273%)
In [70]:
from sklearn.ensemble import BaggingRegressor
pipe_lr2 = Pipeline([('scl', StandardScaler()), ('pca', PCA()), ('brg', BaggingRegressor(random_state=seed))])
results2 = cross_val_score(pipe_lr2, X, y, cv=kfold)
print("Bagging Regressor Accuracy: %.3f%% (%.3f%%)" % (results2.mean()*100.0, results2.std()*100.0))
Results = Results.append([{'Type':'Bagging Regressor','Score':results2.mean()*100.0}])

Bagging Regressor Accuracy: 80.688% (7.374%)
In [71]:
from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestRegressor
rfr = RandomForestRegressor(random_state=seed)
results3 = cross_val_score(rfr, X, y, cv=kfold)
print("Random Forest Regressor Accuracy: %.3f%% (%.3f%%)" % (results3.mean()*100.0, results3.std()*100.0))
Results = Results.append([{'Type':'Random Forest Regressor','Score':results3.mean()*100.0}])

Random Forest Regressor Accuracy: 91.149% (5.344%)

Hyper Parameter tuning using Grid Search and Random Search¶

In [72]:
from sklearn.model_selection import RandomizedSearchCV
parameters3 = {
    'bootstrap': [False,True],
 'max_depth': list(range(35,45)),
    'criterion':['mae','mse'],
     'min_samples_split':[1,2,3,4],
 'max_features': ['auto', 'sqrt','log2'],
    'oob_score': [False,True],
 'min_samples_leaf':  list(range(1,4))}

randomCV3 = RandomizedSearchCV(rfr, param_distributions=parameters3, n_iter=25) #default cv = 3


randomCV3.fit( X_train, y_train)


# print(randomCV3.best_params_)
print("RandomizedSearch with Random Forest Regressor")
print(" Best cross-validation accuracy: {:.2f}". format( randomCV3.best_score_))
print(" Best parameters: ", randomCV3.best_params_)
print(" Test set accuracy: {:.2f}". format( randomCV3.score( X_test, y_test)))
Results = Results.append([{'Type':'Randomized Search Optimized Random Forest Regressor','Score':format( randomCV3.score( X_test, y_test) * 100) }])

RandomizedSearch with Random Forest Regressor
 Best cross-validation accuracy: 0.90
 Best parameters:  {'oob_score': False, 'min_samples_split': 2, 'min_samples_leaf': 1, 'max_features': 'log2', 'max_depth': 40, 'criterion': 'mse', 'bootstrap': False}
 Test set accuracy: 0.90

from sklearn.model_selection import GridSearchCV
# BaggingRegressor()
parameters2 = {
    'brg__n_estimators': [19,20,21],
    'brg__max_samples': [400,425,435],
 'brg__max_features': [6,7,8],
 'brg__bootstrap': [False, True],
}

gridCV2 = GridSearchCV( pipe_lr2 , param_grid = parameters2, cv = 8)


gridCV2.fit( X_train, y_train)


# print(randomCV3.best_params_)
print("Grid Search Bagging Regressor")
print(" Best cross-validation accuracy: {:.2f}". format( gridCV2.best_score_))
print(" Best parameters: ", gridCV2.best_params_)
print(" Test set accuracy: {:.2f}". format( gridCV2.score( X_test, y_test)))

Results = Results.append([{'Type':'Grid Search Optimized Bagging Regressor','Score':format( gridCV2.score( X_test, y_test)* 100)}])
